  "prompt": "What are the best biographies about Bruce Lee?",
  "response": "Here are some highly regarded biographies about Bruce Lee:\n\n1. \"Bruce Lee: A Life\" by Matthew Polly (2018)\n- Considered one of the most comprehensive and well-researched biographies\n- Extensive research and interviews with people who knew Lee personally\n\n2. \"Bruce Lee: The Tao of Gung Fu\" by Bruce Thomas (1996)\n- Focuses on Lee's martial arts philosophy and development\n- Includes insights into his martial arts training and personal thoughts\n\n3. \"Bruce Lee: The Evolution of a Martial Artist\" by Tommy Gong (2013)\n- Provides detailed information about Lee's martial arts techniques and philosophy\n- Written with input from Lee's family and close associates\n\n4. \"Dragon: The Bruce Lee Story\" by Linda Lee Cadwell (1975)\n- A personal account written by Lee's wife\n- Offers intimate insights into his life and personality\n\n5. \"Bruce Lee: The Untold Story\" by Tom Bleecker (1994)\n- Provides a more intimate look at Lee's life\n- Includes perspectives from people who knew him closely\n\nEach of these books offers a different perspective on Bruce Lee's life, making them valuable for understanding his legacy and impact.",
